## C√¢u 7
Gi·∫£i ph∆∞∆°ng tr√¨nh $x^2 - 5x + 6 = 0$

**A)** $x = 2$ ho·∫∑c $x = 3$

**B)** $x = -2$ ho·∫∑c $x = -3$

**C)** $x = 1$ ho·∫∑c $x = 6$

**D)** V√¥ nghi·ªám

**Gi·∫£i:**
$x^2 - 5x + 6 = 0$

$\Delta = 25 - 24 = 1$

$x = \frac{5 \pm \sqrt{1}}{2} = \frac{5 \pm 1}{2}$

$x_1 = 3, x_2 = 2$

V·∫≠y ƒë√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng l√† **A**.

